    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use CG to solve Ax=b when A is symmetric positive-definite (the method may break",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "down or fail to converge if A is not positive-definite).",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For square, full rank unsymmetric or indefinite equations, use GMRES instead.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For rectangular or singular systems, use LSMR instead.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "More information on the CG algorithm can be found on wikipedia:",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjugate_gradient_method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A more detailed review of CG is available in the paper:",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "[1] J. Shewchuk (1994), “An Introduction to the Conjugate Gradient Method Without the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Agonizing Pain”, Technical Report, Carnegie Mellon University.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "@callback reportError Function to use to report parameter errors.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If NULL, errors are logged via <os/log.h> and execution is",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "halted via __builtin_trap().  If non-NULL, the provided function is",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "called with a human-readable string describing the error condition.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If the callback returns, control will be returned to the caller with",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "any outputs in a safe but undefined state (i.e. they may hold partial",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "results or garbage, but all sizes and pointers are valid).",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "\\field maxIterations",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Maximum number of iterations to perform. If 0, the default value of 100",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is used.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "\\field atol",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Absolute convergence tolerance. Iterate is considered to have converged if",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "|| b-Ax ||_2 < rtol * || b-Ax_0 ||_2 + atol.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "\\field rtol",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Relative convergence tolerance. Iterate is considered to have converged if",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "|| b-Ax ||_2 < rtol * || b-Ax_0 ||_2 + atol.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If rtol = 0.0, default value of sqrt(epsilon) is used.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If negative, rtol is treated as 0.0 (default is not used).",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "@callback reportStatus Function to use to report status (iteration count",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and residual of first right-hand side) every few iterations.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If NULL, status is not reported.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
